            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><milestone unit="fragment" n="a"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64402"><name nymRef="#Ἱππόδαμος">Ἱππόδαμος</name> 
                        <milestone unit="fragment" n="b"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64319"><name nymRef="#Ἰάσων" type="patronymic">Ἰάσονος</name></persName></persName>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Hippodamos fils de Iason.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Hippodamos son of Iason.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Hippodamos figlio di Iason.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The holes for attachment of a statue imply that this was no funerary base and the place where the base was found shows that it was a dedication to Apollo.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
